I"<p>This is a quick video of lazy loading working for Angular 6 routes. It is used when routing to feature modules, and stops the modules being initiliased before they are needed.</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: 'customers',
    loadChildren: './customers/customers.module#CustomersModule'
  }
  ]</code></p>

<p>Is how a lazy loaded <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">CustomersModule</code> would look - the key is the loadChildren, and a the path to the to the feature module you want to lazy loaded being entered as a string.</p>
<p style="text-align: center">
